  "content": "ID: T1568.003\nTitle: Dynamic Resolution:DNS Calculation\nURL: https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1568/003\nAdversaries may perform calculations on addresses returned in DNS results to determine which port and IP address to use for command and control, rather than relying on a predetermined port number or the actual returned IP address. A IP and/or port number calculation can be used to bypass egress filtering on a C2 channel. [1] One implementation of DNS Calculation is to take the first three octets of an IP address in a DNS response and use those values to calculate the port for command and control traffic. [1] [2] [3]",
